===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*per-|id=fare|*h₂et-}}
The {{glossary|adjective}} is borrowed from {{bor|en|la|perennis|t=lasting through the whole year or for several years, perennial; continual, everlasting, perpetual}} + [[w:English language|English]] {{m|en|-al|pos={{glossary|suffix}} meaning ‘of or pertaining to’ forming adjectives}}. {{m|la||Perennis}} is derived from {{m|la|per-|t=completive or intensifying {{glossary|prefix}} with the sense of doing something all the way through or entirely}} + {{m|la|annus|t=year; season, time}}<ref>{{R:OED Online|pos=adj.'' and ''n|id=140686|date=March 2022|nodot=1}}; {{R:Lexico|pos=adj.'' and ''n}}</ref> (possibly ultimately from {{der|en|ine-pro|*h₂et-|t=to go}}). The English word is {{glossary|surface analysis|analysable}} as {{confix|en|per|ennial}}.

The {{glossary|noun}} is derived from the adjective.

